A lawmaker in the Bauchi State House of Assembly, Musa Baraza, is dead, According to The PUNCH. It was gathered that Baraza was killed by gunmen on Thursday night at his residence in the Dass Local Government Area. The lawmaker represented Dass Constituency in the House before his murder. The Bauchi State Police Command confirmed the incident on Friday morning. The state Police Public Relations Officer, Ahmed Wakili, said the assailants also kidnapped his two wives and one-year-old child. He gave the names of the two wives and child of the deceased who are still in the custody of their captors. Wakili gave their names as Rashida Musa Mante (40), Rahina Musa Mante (35) while the child’s name is Fausar Musa Mante (1). He added that four empty shells of live ammunitions have been recovered from the scene of the murder. The PPRO, however, said a crack team of police personnel have been mobilised to the area to commence an immediate investigation to rescue the victims and nab the perpetrators. By Huseyn Mbar Bauchi -A member of the Bauchi State House of Assembly representing Baraza/Dass constituency, Alhaji Musa Mante, has been killed by suspected gunmen. A source, who pleaded anonymity, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Bauchi that Mante was killed on Thursday at his residence in Dass.… August 14, 2020 In "News" By Eric James Ochigbo Abuja -  The Speaker of the House of Representatives, Mr. Yakubu Dogara, has described as devastating and heart breaking, the news of the death of Sen. Ali Wakili (APC-Bauchi). In a statement in Abuja on Saturday, Dogara described the late Wakili as “a personal friend, true… March 17, 2018 In "News" By Mohammed Ahmed Kaigama     Bauchi  -    Federal Government’s delegation on Sunday visited Bauchi to commiserate with the state government and family of Sen. Ali Wakili (APC), member representing Bauchi South, who died on Saturday. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the delegation was led by Malam… March 19, 2018 In "News"